2016 WW53 Bakerville/SKX-D Silver Release Announcement (BKC #6)

\n \n \n

DEG Platform Integration Team

\n \n
\n

The DEG platform Integration team announces the release of 2016 WW53 Bakerville/SKX-D Silver release package for Intel internal use. The release is based on OS of\n \n Linux/\n \n VMWare/\n \n Windows\n server. The auto-installer packages are available in the Artifactory server (both SH site and OR site). Any questions please contact Bei, Ling.

Test Result:

\xc2\xb7       Finish Silver test execution on\nRHEL 7.2 , Windows2016 and VMware. Please visit HPQC for test details. Refer to the installation guide for\nthe BKC package installation

\xc2\xb7      Bakerville(RP Board: Yuba\nCity RP\nfab3)

o   Total test cases: 22; Passed test cases is 20 and pass\nrate is 90.91%. 

o   Test coverage:  

\xc2\xa7     SKX-D L0 VIS SoC: Run P1 and P2 test cases on RHEL 7.2 and Windows2016.

HW rework:
  • No HW rework need for Yuba City fab3 board.
  • jumper setting refers to this link.
Work around:

  • When you flash onboard Aspeed BMC, in order to detect onboard dTPM in AC cycle, you need run below IPMI command in UEFI Shell:
            #cmdtool  20 C0 3f 07

InformationQuick Guide
BKC Artifactory Access

Link (SH server): https://ubit-artifactory-sh.intel.com

Link (OR server): https://ubit-artifactory-or.intel.com

Steps for applying the permission:

  • Go to EAM website:http://eam.intel.com/EAMWeb/default.aspx
  • Click on "Add or Remove access"
  • Navigate to:"Enterprise Applications - DevTools - DEG_Purley"
  • Apply for the "Project viewer" role
  • Use your windows credentials for authentication

BKC One Stop Shop

Link: https://dcg-oss.intel.com

Steps for applying the permission:

  • Go to EAM website: http://eam.intel.com/EAMWeb/default.aspx
  • Click on "Add or Remove access"
  • Navigate to:"Enterprise Applications - CI Automation u2013 One Stop Shop (OSS) u2013 BKC u2013 Purley"
  • Apply for the "User" or "Ingredient Owner" role
  • Use your windows credentials for authentication

Contact Person: Bei, Ling
